"{\"uid\": \"odnako.org-the-olympic-torch-travels-towards-paris-and-also-crosses-the-strait-of-messina-escorted-by-the-coast-guard\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Sport  By John  2024-05-03  The French sailing ship Belem, on which theOlympic torchbound for Marseille, has recently faced navigation in one of the busiest stretches of sea in the world, loStrait of Messina, also accompanied by naval and aerial vehicles of the Coast Guard which supervise and monitor navigation in this delicate maritime hub.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 343, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 52, \"end\": 57, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"score\": 0.9903282791600577, \"rank\": 0.00799898425596817, \"text\": \"Belem\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bel\\u00e9m\"}, {\"begin\": 94, \"end\": 103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"score\": 0.9999997936290796, \"rank\": 1.9248883069452074e-07, \"text\": \"Marseille\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marseille\"}, {\"begin\": 200, \"end\": 207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Messina\", \"score\": 0.999999972123533, \"rank\": 2.7867649542302457e-08, \"text\": \"Messina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Messina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Messina\"}, {\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 273, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\", \"score\": 0.9945241653203711, \"rank\": 0.0048956733610088345, \"text\": \"Coast Guard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The convoy is constantly followed by the Messina Coast Guard, Maritime Authority of the Strait, from whose Vts (Vessel Traffic Service) control center there is a continuous exchange of communications useful for guaranteeing the safety of navigation of both the Olympic torch and any other vessel passes through the area.\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Messina\", \"score\": 0.999999972123533, \"rank\": 2.7867649542302457e-08, \"text\": \"Messina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Messina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Messina\"}, {\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\", \"score\": 0.9945241653203711, \"rank\": 0.0048956733610088345, \"text\": \"Coast Guard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The VTS center of the Coast Guard uses modern technological tools and sophisticated sensors to monitor the numerous merchant and recreational traffic that takes place in the stretch of sea that separates Sicily from Calabria.\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 892, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 689, \"end\": 700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\", \"score\": 0.9945241653203711, \"rank\": 0.0048956733610088345, \"text\": \"Coast Guard\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Coast_Guard\"}, {\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calabria\", \"score\": 0.9980288528860153, \"rank\": 0.001971775932545839, \"text\": \"Calabria\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calabria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Calabria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With VTS, data relating to the presence and